===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|quaveren|lang=enm}}, frequentative form of {{term|quaven|lang=enm}}, {{term|cwavien||to tremble|lang=enm}}, equivalent to {{suffix|quave|er}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|quabbeln||to quiver|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|quabbeln|lang=de}}, {{term|quappeln||to quiver|lang=de}}. More at {{l|en|quave}}, {{l|en|quab}}, {{l|en|quiver}}.

===Pronunciation===
*: {{rhymes|eɪvə(r)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a [[trembling]] shake.
# a trembling of the voice, as in speaking or singing.
# {{context|music|lang=en}} an [[eighth note]], drawn as a [[crotchet]] ([[quarter note]]) with a tail.

